# Selection Controls - KX Dashboards

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/dashboards/selectioncontrols/

# Selection Controls

![Screenshot](../img/selection/selectsectorradio.jpg)  
_Some Radio Buttons_

## Set up

  1. Use a data source to define the items in the selection control.

  2. Define in the mapping which column represents the text labels in the selection control, and which column is the value passed to the view state on selection. 

  3. Set the _Selected Value_ as a [view state parameter](../viewstateparameters/) which carries the value of the selected item. 

## Basics

![Screenshot](../img/selection/radiobuttonsbasic.png)

_Name_

    A name for the component provided by the user. 
_Data Source_

    

A [data source](../datasources/): include the list of values to pass into the
linked [View State Parameter](../viewstateparameters/) and possibly a list of
value names to display in the dropdown. For example:

![Screenshot](../img/selection/dropdowndatasourcehtmllight.jpg)  
_A query for a Radio Button data source_

Tip

When using _Data Source_ to create a set of radio buttons, ensure _Use Data
Source_ is checked and _Data Source Mapping_ is defined.

    

A sample query to use is (if connecting to the sample data connection source
`htmlevalcongroup` available in the sample demo dashboard set):

`q select distinct src from dfxQuote`

_Selected Value_

    

The view state parameter populated on selection.

[Selected values](../viewstateparameters/#selected-values)

_Label_

    Label description for the Radio Button
_Use Data Source_

    When checked, _Data Source_ is used to build a Radio Button
_Accept Empty Values_

    When checked, a null value is available for selection
_Force Selected Value_

    When checked, the Radio Button will always populate a _Selected Value_ [View State Parameter](../viewstateparameters/); either default or selected value (which may be null if not set). 
_Multi-select_

    

When checked, multiple radio button selections are supported and selected
items passed to the _Selected Value_ View State Parameter.

![Screenshot](../img/selection/mutliselectradio.jpg)

_Items Layout_

    Configure Radio Button layout: `Horizontal` or `Vertical`
_Horizontal_

    Radio button alignment: `Left`, `Right` or `Center`
_Vertical_

    Radio button alignment: `Top`, `Middle` or `Bottom`
_Label Width_

    Width of the main label
_Item Action Event_

    Sets the type of action event when useDatasource is set to false

  * none : (default) no action when changing a selection
  * always : always runs actions when changing a selection
  * index - only run actions when changing to the selected index
  * value - only run actions when changing to the selected value

## Data source mapping

![Screenshot](../img/selection/datasourcemapping.jpg)

When a _Data Source_ is used to populate Radio Buttons, the items of the _Data
Source_ will represent values. Labels must be assigned using _Data Source
Mapping_ â€“ else the list will be empty.

_Value_

    The column of the _Data Source_ corresponding to the values to be passed into the _Selected Value_ View State Parameter
_Text_

    The column of the _Data Source_ corresponding to the text to be displayed as the dropdown options

## Items

![Screenshot](../img/selection/itemsdropdownlist.jpg)

If _Data Source_ is not used to create Radio Buttons, individual values can be
specified in the _Items_ menu.

## Action

[Actions](../action/)

## Style

_Template_

![Screenshot](../img/selection/selectioncontrol_template.png)

    

Sets the label text for each selection item. The parameters passed to the
template depend on whether _Use Data Source_ is enabled.

  * if using a data source then the parameters reflect the column names
  * if inputting items manually then Text and Value parameters are passed

